## Terminology

The key words "MUST", "MUST NOT", "REQUIRED", "SHALL", "SHALL NOT",
"SHOULD", "SHOULD NOT", "RECOMMENDED", "MAY", and "OPTIONAL" in this
document are to be interpreted as described in [RFC 2119].

| Term | Definition |
|------|-----------|
| Identity Commitment | Poseidon hash of the identity secret; serves as the leaf in the Merkle tree |
| Nullifier | Domain-separated hash preventing double-use of a proof |
| Scope Bitmask | 64-bit field encoding permitted operation scopes for delegated identities |
| Delegation Chain | Ordered sequence of delegation proofs from a human root to an agent leaf |

